==Old Content== {{Commons category}} {{Category main article}} '''Afterlife''' is the concept that an [[:en:Essence|essential part]] of an individual's [[:en:Personal identity|identity]] or the [[Stream of consciousness (psychology)|stream of consciousness]] continues to manifest after the [[:en:Death|Death]] of the physical body. According to various ideas about the afterlife, the essential aspect of the individual that lives on after death may be some partial element, or the entire [[soul]] or spirit, of an individual, which carries with it and may confer personal identity or, on the contrary, may not, as in Indian [[nirvana]]. Belief in an afterlife, which may be [[:en:Naturalism (philosophy)|naturalistic]] or [[supernatural]], is in contrast to the belief in [[:en:Eternal oblivion|oblivion after death]]. {{draft categories|
}}
